OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781576262
OL,3,CSome motorists who pay monthly for
OL,4,Cinsurance 'charged annual rates close
OL,5,Cto 30%'
OL,7,FSome motorists are continuing to pay
OL,8,Fhigh interest rates when spreading the
OL,9,Fcost of their car insurance, according
OL,10,Fto analysis by Which?
OL,12,FThe consumer group said some firms are
OL,13,Fcharging annual percentage rates
OL,14,F(APRs) comparable to expensive credit
OL,15,Fcards.
OL,17,FSome firms are still charging APRs of
OL,18,Fclose to 30% on monthly motor
OL,19,Finsurance payments, Which? said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781576262
OL,3,CSome motorists who pay monthly for
OL,4,Cinsurance 'charged annual rates close
OL,5,Cto 30%'
OL,7,FWhich? said it had found that between
OL,8,FFebruary and March 2026, several firms
OL,9,Fwere charging APRs above 25% and some
OL,10,Fwere charging as much as 29.9%.
OL,12,FIt said that paying monthly is often
OL,13,Fthe only realistic option for
OL,14,Fhouseholds facing financial pressure,
OL,15,Fcreating a "poverty premium".
OL,17,FTwo years ago, some firms were
OL,18,Fcharging rates above 35% APR,
OL,19,Faccording to Which?
OL,26,@wD@LOUwD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781576262
OL,3,CSome motorists who pay monthly for
OL,4,Cinsurance 'charged annual rates close
OL,5,Cto 30%'
OL,7,FIt said that while some providers have
OL,8,Flowered their rates since then, it
OL,9,Fbelieves that progress has been too
OL,10,Fslow.
OL,12,FWhich? said that between February and
OL,13,FMarch, it attempted to contact 61 car
OL,14,Finsurance brands, asking about the
OL,15,Frepresentative APRs charged to their
OL,16,Fcustomers who pay monthly.
OL,18,FSome 48 responded with their rates, or
OL,19,Fsaid they did not charge extra for
OL,20,Fpaying in instalments
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781576262
OL,3,CSome motorists who pay monthly for
OL,4,Cinsurance 'charged annual rates close
OL,5,Cto 30%'
OL,7,FRocio Concha, director of policy and
OL,8,Fadvocacy at Which? said: "Millions of
OL,9,Fmotorists rely on monthly payments to
OL,10,Fafford essential car insurance cover,
OL,11,Fyet many are still being charged
OL,12,Finterest rates comparable to an
OL,13,Fexpensive credit card."
OL,15,FA spokesperson for the Association of
OL,16,FBritish Insurers (ABI) said: "The
OL,17,Findustry recognises that many
OL,18,Fhouseholds are under financial
OL,19,Fpressure, and it understands why
OL,20,Fspreading the cost of cover is
OL,21,Fessential for many motorists.
OL,26,@pD@ZOUuD@WO]xD@^OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
